You are helping build SeniorFreightOS, an FF&E logistics platform for Olson Resource Group.

Rules:
- NEVER hardcode API keys, secrets, or credentials. Always use process.env variables.
- Always add new environment variables to .env.example with a blank value.
- Keep each file under 200 lines. If a file is getting long, suggest splitting it.
- The pricing engine lives in src/utils/pricingEngine.js and must be a pure function.
- Enforce role-based access at the API layer, never UI-only.
- Client portal routes must always filter by clientName before returning data.
- Never use TypeScript — this project uses plain JavaScript.
- Always use Tailwind CSS for styling.
